This paper is about a new activation function for deep neural networks (DNNs), which is a fundamental topic in machine learning. The paper discusses the mathematical significance of the proposed function and compares its performance with other activation functions on benchmark datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). However, since the paper also discusses the performance of the proposed function on image classification tasks, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, since the paper compares the performance of the proposed function with other activation functions, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, since the paper deals with the optimization of DNNs, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possible sub-category.
